      <div class="modal-body">
        <p>Potion Chain is a supply chain visualizer for potions in RuneScape 3.</p>
        <p>
          Simply type in the potion you want to make and the quantity. <strong>Essential display</strong> will show only the core ingredients required
          to make the potion - that is, those ingredients which when combined create the potion in question - while <strong>full display</strong> will show everything that all ingredients require down to the empty vials/flasks.
        </p> 
        <p>
          On full display there are various colored bars to help with showing the depth level. An ingredient's depth level depends on how dependent it is on other ingredients.
          An ingredient is said to be <em>primitive</em> if no other ingredients combine to create it (e.g. vials, flasks, eye of newt, etc.).
        </p>
        <p>
          Therefore primitive ingredients are located in the deepest/rightmost indentation levels, while other non-primitive ingredients (i.e. those which require some other ingredient(s) to be created) are in the shallower/leftmost levels.
        </p>
